When Clinton’s supporters are asked why they want her to be the candidate, the most common answer is that she has the right experience (16 percent), followed by the belief that it’s time for a woman to become president (13 percent) and that she’s the best candidate for the job (10 percent).
Clinton’s supporters also mention her connection with Bill Clinton (9 percent).
Approval for dealing with the problems and the electability are also cited.
As the vice president throws a potential for president, 57 percent of the Democratic voters of the primaries want to see him in the race – although one-third believe he shouldn’t.
When Democratic voters of the primaries are asked who would be their second choice for the party, Biden is at the top.
